		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Semper affectans
						spiritus, &agrave; verbo
						in verbu[m] animet
						singula dicta:
						singulaq[ue] facta &agrave; 
						principio ad 
						medium, &agrave; 
						medio ad finem.
						Sed fluentissima 
						omniu[m] faciltate.
						Sola enim pulchr&egrave; fiu[n]t,
						qua[e] fiunt facil&egrave;: et
						ea tandem pra[e]clara,
						qua[e] reuera
						) su[n]t
						excellentissima.
						Ca[e]tera aliqua ben&egrave;:
						) sed non satis ben&egrave;:
						optim&egrave;, sed apud vulgares
						optim&egrave;. Requiritur
						in triplici Entelechia, pulcherrima
						mundi Euschemosyne: et
						in rebus secundis
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						( candidissim&egrave; magnifica:
						nec vllo turbido casu, aut aduersa tempestate
						deflorescens. Semper deniq[ue] splendidissima.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Let the spirit, ever striving, animate singular sayings word by word,
				and animate singular deeds from beginning to middle, middle to end.
				However, this with the most fluid facility regarding all matters.
				Only those matters which happen easily happen beautifully;
				and those matters which are, in fact, most excellent, are splendid.
				Other matters are sometimes done well, but not well enough;
				excellently, but only excellently among the common people. 
				Refinement is required in triple Actualization, the most beautiful thing
				in the world and most brightly splendid in good fortune.
				And it does not wither in any chaotic calamities or hostile tempest.
				Indeed, it is always most splendid.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
